title: liquid drum and bass, soulful
caption: liquid drum and bass, soulful female topline, jazzy chords, smooth melodic delivery, rolling breakbeats, atmospheric
lyrics:
[Verse 1]
I choose the wrong moments, trip through time, pretend it’s discipline
Every step arrives crooked, nothing syncs the way it’s meant to
I memorized the gaps, not the order they were selling me
Learned to breathe in misalignment when the certainty gives in

[Pre-Chorus]
I don’t chase alignment
I don’t wait for signs
I stand inside the error
And call the damage mine

[Chorus]
Nothing ever lands where it should
But imbalance is how I keep standing
Nothing ever feels understood
I stay upright by never landing

[Verse 2]
I count the pauses louder than the moments that appear
Trust the miss more than the hit, let confusion steer
Every correction pulls me under, every rule feels thin
So I lean into the stagger and let the fall begin

[Pre-Chorus]
I stopped asking permission
From patterns that collapse
I move against the promise
That order ever lasts

[Chorus]
Nothing ever lands where it should
But imbalance is how I keep standing
Nothing ever feels understood
I stay upright by never landing

[Bridge]
If this breaks me, let it be deliberate
If I slip, let it look designed
I don’t need a center to keep moving
I survive by losing the line

[Break]
Wrong moment
Wrong step
Still here
Still held

[Chorus – Final]
Nothing ever lands where it should
But imbalance is how I keep standing
Nothing ever feels understood
I stay upright by never landing

[Outro]
I don’t fall apart
I fall in pattern
Just unstable enough
To stay upright
